{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3f343bda-245d-4a5c-8734-e0ec0ba1108a","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet --version` to confirm the SDK, then `dotnet build` to catch any breaking API changes. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for any breaking changes relevant to your dependencies.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2209b951-4006-4280-ba2b-38426a84ba06","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the three items they mentioned.","outputTokens":289,"requestId":"300C:301399:174993E:1A038DA:6A067B6B"},"id":"3e0eab14-47ea-4e0b-a08d-94690f0758f3","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:48:33.286Z","parentId":"3980636d-d477-4073-9288-866ad7d4c63e"}
